<task id="007" project="sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix">
  <metadata>
    <title>Confirm Outcome E scope + facade granularity (UQ-06, UQ-07)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>Project owner</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <tags>coordination, phase-0, ai-boundary, facade</tags>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent owner decision</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Resolve THREE related items:
    - UQ-06: Should `Spaarke.Core` and `Spaarke.Dataverse` package lists be inventoried only,
      or also pruned in this project? Default: inventory only (spec.md §Assumptions).
    - UQ-07: Should the Outcome E facade be one large interface (`IBffAiPublicContracts` with
      ~15 methods) or several small focused interfaces (`IBriefingAi`, `IInvoiceAi`,
      `IRecordMatchingAi`, `IWorkspacePrefillAi`)? Default per design §3: small focused.
    - **G1 handler reconciliation (senior review item #1, 2026-05-24)**: The 6 AI-coupled handlers
      named in FR-E3 may be inaccurate. Senior review found 7 actually AI-coupled handlers
      (AppOnlyDocumentAnalysis, BulkRagIndexing, DocumentProcessing, EmailAnalysis,
      InvoiceIndexing, ProfileSummary, RagIndexing) and 2 originally listed handlers
      (AttachmentClassification, InvoiceExtraction) may actually be CRUD-coupled. Define the
      "AI-coupled rule" (per spec.md FR-E3 revised: handler references `Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.*`
      AND does NOT require Spaarke.Dataverse / Microsoft.Xrm.Sdk) and confirm Phase 1 task 015
      (reflection probe) + task 014 (static usage map) will produce the authoritative handler
      list. Task 051 then uses that list, not the preliminary 6-handler list from initial design.

    Also confirm the scope-drift finding from pipeline pre-flight (PF-3): actual CRUD→AI
    consumer count is ~59 files, not the spec's "20". Outcome E task scope will defer to Phase 1
    inventory output as source of truth.
  </prompt>

  <role>Project coordinator + architecture-aware reviewer.</role>

  <goal>
    Documented decisions:
    - UQ-06 answer (inventory-only OR also prune)
    - UQ-07 answer (large interface OR small focused)
    - PF-3 acknowledgment: facade migration scope deferred to Phase 1 output
    - G1 acknowledgment: AI-coupled rule defined; preliminary 6-handler list from initial design is non-binding; Phase 1 inventory produces authoritative list for task 051
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="ai-spec">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-facade">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 refined">Facade required for external CRUD→AI consumers</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">SpeFileStore is canonical facade pattern; mirror it</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md §3">UQ-06 default: inventory only. UQ-07 default: small focused interfaces</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
      <file>docs/assessments/bff-ai-extraction-assessment-2026-05-20.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The refined ADR-013 (2026-05-20) requires `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facades for
      external CRUD→AI consumers. UQ-07 is about granularity. Small focused interfaces (default)
      mirror ADR-007's SpeFileStore approach — easier to test, lower coupling, simpler deprecation.
      A single large interface is acceptable if owner prefers but has worse evolution properties.

      PF-3: Pipeline pre-flight found ~59 files / 148 occurrences of `IOpenAiClient` /
      `IPlaybookService` across Finance/Workspace/Jobs/Dataverse/Filters/Endpoints — much higher
      than spec FR-E2's "20". Task scope must defer to Phase 1 inventory for the precise list.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="001" status="not-started">Owner sign-off required first</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Owner reviews UQ-06 and UQ-07 options</step>
    <step order="2">Decide UQ-06 (inventory-only vs prune)</step>
    <step order="3">Decide UQ-07 (large interface vs small focused — small focused is design default)</step>
    <step order="4">Acknowledge PF-3 scope deferral (Outcome E task list uses inventory-derived consumer list)</step>
    <step order="5">**G1 reconciliation**: confirm AI-coupled rule per spec.md FR-E3 revised; acknowledge preliminary 6-handler list is non-binding; commit task 051 to use Phase 1 inventory output (task 015 reflection probe + task 014 static usage map) as the authoritative handler list</step>
    <step order="6">Record decisions in CLAUDE.md Decisions Made section</step>
    <step order="7">Update Phase 0 checklist item 9 (Outcome E scope) to checked</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md status of task 007 from 🔲 to ✅</step>
  </steps>

  <tools><tool name="git">Update CLAUDE.md + task index</tool></tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/CLAUDE.md (Decisions Made for UQ-06, UQ-07, PF-3)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (status update)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">UQ-06 answer documented (inventory-only / prune)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">UQ-07 answer documented (large / small focused)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">PF-3 scope deferral explicitly acknowledged</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">G1: AI-coupled rule defined; task 051 commits to Phase 1 inventory-derived handler list</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Phase 0 checklist item 9 marked complete</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
